A furphy is Australian slang for a rumour, or an erroneous or improbable story. It derives from Furphy carts, used to transport water during World War I, around which servicemen would gather and gossip, spreading tall stories and rumours.  (this definition was copied from the wikipedia:Furphy page.)

Syn.  US english "scuttle butt"

